name: Traffic Jam (RUN)
overview: Traffic Jam is an "avoid-it" style game in which your goal is to cross the road from the bottom of the screen to the top in order to get to your house, while avoiding cars and other obstacles. The game was developed by Jeffrey D. Panicki and published in ReRun 1990/01-02. ITS FRIDAY. FIVE O'CLOCK. The heaviest traffic of the week, and you have to walk home, crossing seven lanes of speeding cars as you go. If that weren't enough, your dinner is cooking in the oven and you've got only 40 seconds before it burns up. Another day in the big city. Aarrgghh! That's the scenario for Traffic Jam, a fast-paced arcade-style game
